Class AssignmentExpression

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sodacan.module.statement.ModuleComponent

        • net.sodacan.module.expression.BinaryOperator
          • net.sodacan.module.expression.AssignmentExpression
  • public class AssignmentExpression
extends BinaryOperator
    An assignment expression is a bit different from other binary operators in that only the right-hand-side of the assignment is "resolved" and then executed and the resulting value is assigned to the variable on the left side of the assignment.
    Author:
    John Churin
